    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-29T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-29T09:00:00-05:00" n="496"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851A.01/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at St. Pierre-Miquelon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pasquet</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Pierre-Miquelon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-29T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 29, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to the Consulate’s despatch of December 26, No. 79, plebiscite Miquelon
                    held yesterday: 69 in favor of Free France, 4 collaboration, 72 void, total vote
                    of islands of St. Pierre-Miquelon 783, 14, 215 respectively. Submarine patrols
                    coasts during the night.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pasquet</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
